{
  "texts": [
    "The resulting confusion matrix is shown in the left part of Figure 17, and the scores are shown in Table 9.",
    "The classifier struggles to correctly identify the \"WaterW\" cases based on the expression \"Weather.\"",
    "Also, it seems that the expression \"Misc\" may not be the optimal choice, as it produces many false positives.",
    "To address this, we introduce the following heuristic: if the probability assigned to the expression \"Misc\" is highest but with a margin of less than 50 percentage points to the second-most likely expression, we select the latter.",
    "This increases the accuracy score from 65.5% to 69.7% and produces the confusion matrix shown in the right part of Figure 17."
  ]
}